    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix HARQ process error in IF4p5 northbound interface for NR RRU\n\n### Summary\nThe `fh_if4p5_north_out` function in the NR RU processing was incorrectly sending IF4p5 PULFFT packets during downlink and mixed slots in TDD mode. This caused downstream HARQ process errors due to incorrect retransmission timing and wrong redundancy version handling.\n\nThe issue was that the function always sent PULFFT regardless of slot type, unlike the LTE version which properly sends PULTICK during non-uplink slots. This led to the central unit expecting uplink data at wrong times.\n\n### Changes\n- `executables/nr-ru.c`: \n  - Added include for `SCHED_NR/phy_frame_config_nr.h` to access `nr_slot_select`\n  - Modified `fh_if4p5_north_out` to check slot type using `nr_slot_select`\n  - For TDD mode, now sends IF4p5_PULTICK during DL/mixed slots instead of PULFFT\n  - Only sends IF4p5_PULFFT during actual uplink slots\n  - Added logging for better debugging\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Configure NR RRU with IF4p5 interface in TDD mode\n2. Run traffic with mixed slot configuration (both DL and UL slots)\n3. Monitor HARQ process behavior - incorrect retransmissions and wrong RV handling will be observed\n4. Check fronthaul logs for PULFFT packets being sent during DL slots\n\nThe fix ensures proper TDD slot type handling matching the LTE implementation pattern.\n"
}